Review.Titre: This is a good tool for lazy people.
Review.Contenu: This is a good tool for everyday practice. I am a lazy person, and not unusual for skipping for days without practice. Second, you can ask your question on English words that you cannot make out in written dictionaries. Answers you get are personal and hard to go out of your mind elsewhere.Third and last, I make the same mistakes over and over again. Maybe I started correcting my voice too late. I am struggling how to pronounce as effortlessly as possible to be understood. That is the kind of practice I need to repeat, albeit late. Nothing can be late in life if you are determined to speak without accent.

Review.Titre: Great App, not yet to it's fullest potential
Review.Contenu: The app offers an excellent platform for English practice. I appreciate the interactive features, such as chatting with AI and receiving feedback on pronunciation.While I found that the app sometimes inaccurately identifies mispronunciations, it does catch genuine errors. Though there are additional features I'd like to see implemented, the app already has strong potential. It's a valuable tool for language practice and is worth the investment.
